comment.string: "Validation model for multi zone VAV AHU outdoor and return air damper position modulation sequence"
"Control signal for supply air temperature loop"
"Economizer modulation sequence if the dampers positions prevent freezing at the mixed air"
"Outdoor damper if freeze protection is on"
"Return damper position if freeze protection is on"

primarys.simple_primary:
"

This example validates Buildings.Controls.OBC.ASHRAE.G36_PR1.AHUs.MultiZone.Economizers.Subsequences.Modulation for a varying supply air temperature control loop signal. The instance mod is in normal operation, whereas for the instance modFre, the damper limits are as if the mixed air temperature were below its freezing set point.

"

"
  • October 13, 2017, by Michael Wetter:
    Added additional instance to validate the behavior when dampers are such positioned that they prevent the mixed air temperature from being below the freezing set point.
  • June 30, 2017, by Milica Grahovac:
    First implementation.
"
